</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Female</emphasis>
(paratype). General features and colouration similar to those of male (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">14D, E</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 1.39; carapace 0.65 long, 0.56 wide; abdomen 0.72 long, 0.61 wide. Leg measurements: I missing, II 3.46 (0.90, 0.19, 0.99, 0.85, 0.53), III 2.96 (0.76, 0.19, 0.81, 0.75, 0.45), IV 4.40 (1.10, 0.20, 1.30, 1.14, 0.66). Epigastric area (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">14B</figureCitation>
): elliptical dark brown patch. Endogyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">14A</figureCitation>
) with a pair sloped tubular spermathecae, medially with vertical spiral ducts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
